Class Collector

    • Collector
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Runnable

    public class Collector
extends Object
implements Runnable
    This generates random numbers and stores them in a buffer, which simulates data transmission with the Hubble Space Telescope
    Author:
    Andrew Huber

    • Field Detail

      • A

        public static final int A
        The smallest number that this Collector's random number generator can generate. This is used by Processor to normalize the data that is generated. The nomenclature of this variable follows a video tutorial on data normalization that I used as a basis for my data normalization algorithm. The aforementioned video can be found here.
